 <info>
  <link type="guide" xref="index#setup"/>
  <desc>Setup backups to remote servers and online services</desc>
 </info>
 <title>Remote and Online Backups</title>
 <p><app>Pika Backup</app> supports backing up to remote servers and online services with <app>BorgBackup</app>, <cmd>ssh</cmd> or <cmd>sftp</cmd> support. Services with <app>BorgBackup</app> support are recommended for performance reasons.</p>
 <note style="tip">
  <p>For network shares without explicit <app>BorgBackup</app> support, follow <link xref="setup-gvfs"/></p>
 </note>
 <steps>
  <item>
   <p>Select the <gui>Setup Backup</gui> button</p>
   <media type="image" src="media/setup-button.svg"/>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Select <gui>Create New Repository</gui> or <gui>Use Existing Repository</gui></p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Choose <gui>Remote Location</gui></p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Enter the repository URL. This is usually provided by the online backup service if it has explicit <app>BorgBackup</app> support.</p>
   <note style="advanced">
    <title>Syntax</title>
    <p><code>ssh://user@host:port/./path/to/repo</code> - path relative to current directory</p>
    <p><code>ssh://user@host:port/~/path/to/repo</code> - path relative to user’s home directory</p>
    <p><code>ssh://user@host:port/~other/path/to/repo</code> - path relative to other’s home directory</p>
   </note>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Press <gui style="button">Continue</gui></p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Choose the desired <link xref="general-glossary#encryption">encryption</link> settings</p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Press <gui style="button">Create</gui></p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Configure the <gui>Files to Back Up</gui> and <gui>Exclude from Backup</gui> sections</p>
  </item>
  <item>
   <p>Press <gui style="button">Back Up Now</gui></p>
  </item>
 </steps>
</page>
